text:
Start Slideshow Â» CHICAGO - OCTOBER 12: A.J. Pierzynski #12 of the Chicago White Sox runs to first base as catcher Josh Paul #8 tosses the ball on the field in the ninth inning assuming Pierzynski was called out in Game Two of the American League Championship Series against Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim on October 12, 2005 at U.S. Cellular Field in Chicago, Illinois. The inning was extended and the White Sox went on to win 3-1 and tied the series 1-1. (Photo by Stephen Dunn/Getty Images) *** Local Caption *** A.J. Pierzynski;Josh Paul
Manager Ozzie Guillen of the Chicago White Sox jokes with Vladimir Guerrero prior to the start of Game Two of the American League Championship Series. (Photo by Jonathan Daniel/Getty Images)
A.J. Pierzynski runs to first base as catcher Josh Paul tosses the ball on the field in the ninth inning assuming Pierzynski was called out. The inning was extended and the White Sox went on to win 3-1 and tied the series 1-1. (Photo by Stephen Dunn/Getty Images)
